So, the files are in a .RAR file, which is added to a split RAR file, each of which are added to a ZIP file? And every zip file has a copy of the same .NFO and file_id.diz? I thought people stopped doing that when we got rid of floppy disks. Compressing it once saves on download time, but the two additional compression steps just make everyone frustrated. 

It seems to work fine, though, once you manage to get everything extracted, so I still recommend this download.
